    "title": "Tech for Permissive Commons"
  }, "Tech for Permissive Commons"), "")), mdx("p", null, "The \u2018permissive commons\u2019 components are thought to be undeveloped as of today. The principal concept is to support private operation of AI agents; that require data-sets (knowledge / information) relating to various fields of knowledge of mankind.\xA0 Historically, a component of this field is known as \u2018open data\u2019; yet, \u2018permissive commons\u2019 elevates the capacities in new ways to support various new features & benefits; both, in relation to the curation of the knowledge of human-kind, but also, in relation to the means through which we support how AI Agents function.  "), mdx("p", null, "Permissive commons is amongst the greatest of all use-cases for DLTs (decentralised Ledger Technologies, ie: DHTs & Blockchains); including via DIDs (decentralised IDentifiers) to support RDF resources being made available via protocols other than HTTP.\xA0"), mdx("ol", {
